    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-07T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-07T18:00:00-05:00" n="55"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d55">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 600.119/603b</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-07T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 7, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6797. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 165. Supplementing and amending Nos. 113 and 154.<note n="1" xml:id="d55fn1"
                        >The latter not printed.</note> We proposed issuing with discretion “Z”
                    licenses without reference to London for: <pb facs="0137" n="971"
                        xml:id="pg_971"/>
                    <list>
                        <label>(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                        <item>Reasonable quantities of any commodities for the Diplomatic, Consular,
                            Army and Navy officials of the United States and of any friendly
                            country;</item>
                        <label>(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                        <item>Personal effects, household goods, and other small articles of
                            personal property of similar character;</item>
                        <label>(<hi rend="italic">c</hi>)</label>
                        <item>Samples of commodities of all kinds including commodities that may be
                            on the embargo list providing they are of no commercial value;</item>
                        <label>(<hi rend="italic">d</hi>)</label>
                        <item>Articles of small value used solely for advertising purposes provided
                            they are consigned to the American Consul at point of destination for
                            purpose of censorship;</item>
                        <label>(<hi rend="italic">e</hi>)</label>
                        <item>Foodstuffs consigned to the citizens of the United States and the
                            Allied countries sojourning abroad, not exceeding $20 in value for any
                            one shipment.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>It is proposed to issue these “Z” licenses only in exceptional cases. We propose
                    issuing such licenses immediately. We have consulted the British Embassy, who
                    have agreed, subject to approval from the Foreign Office.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
